    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "that makes sense. but i've seen a lot of people online saying the UN is basically just a dead institution at this point because it can't even stop the big powers from doing whatever they want. do historians see that kind of criticism as a valid structural critique of how the whole thing is set up, or is it more of an unrealistic view of how global diplomacy is supposed to work?",
